<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05036j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05036j">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05036j"> 36(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Edify me &mdash;</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Presently the sound of voices reached their strained ears, and what he calls &lsquo;a hole horror&rsquo; overpowered them. Two more hours passed, and the Saint opened the door and came out. Sulpicius was on terms of peculiar familiarity with him, and he ventured to ask him to <mark>edify him</mark> and Brother Gallus by telling them whom he had been talking to in his cell. <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 95</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
